        </div>
    
        <div class="lightBlack">
            <h2 class="smallerTitle">How Does the Pomodoro Technique work?</h2>
            <p>This technique is a time management method that will help you hyperfocus on tasks by
                working at predetermined intervals followed by brief moments of rest. It's akin to running a 
                marathon rather than a 100-meter dash. You chip away at your tasks one by one until you're
                all done. Always remember: you don't have to do all of it as long as you did some of it.</p>
        </div>
    
        <div class="lightBlack">
            <h2 class="smallerTitle">How to Use the Pomodoro Technique</h2>
            <ol class="numerList">
                <li>Decide on the task to be done.</li>
                <li>Set the pomodoro timer (typically for 25 minutes).</li>
                <li>Work on the task</li>
                <li>If you have finished fewer than three pomodoros, go back to Step 2 and repeat until you go through all three pomodoros.</li>
                <li>After three pomodoros are done, take the fourth pomodoro and then take a long break (typically 20 to 30 minutes). Once the long break is finished, return to step</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    
